<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B13FFDFFC89F518FBA1F4CC" pageId="13" pageNumber="524" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B13FFDFFC89F518FB3CF609" blockId="13.[796,1391,2409,2832]" pageId="13" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B13FFDFFC89F518FC28F65A" bold="true" box="[797,952,2409,2438]" pageId="13" pageNumber="524">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B13FFDFFC4DF518FCF1F672" authority="Thomas" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1916" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="13" pageNumber="524" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="porteousi">Ctenomys porteousi Thomas, 1916</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="61F1F00F1B13FFDFFCE7F5E4FB3CF609" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798388369" pageId="13" pageNumber="524">“Bonifacio, SSW. Buenos Ayres Province, about 36°49’ S, 62° W.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B13FFDFFCB4F5AAFBA1F4CC" blockId="13.[796,1391,2409,2832]" pageId="13" pageNumber="524">
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B13FFDFFCB4F5AAFB82F620" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1916" box="[800,1042,2523,2556]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="13" pageNumber="524" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="porteousi">Ctenomys porteousi</taxonomicName>
belongs to the mendocinus-species group based on biogeography and mtDNA phylogeny. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 46-48 and FN = 71-73, and sperm form is simple asymmetric. Twelve different haplotypes have been found, determining a phylogeographic pattern. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B13FFDFFF2DF768FC50F4EA" box="[185,960,2841,2870]" pageId="13" pageNumber="524" type="distribution">
